# INCREMENTS — Agent context

## What this is

**Cognitive orchestration** for a high-output operator — not a productivity app, habit tracker, or motivation product.

Core job: remove **execution drag** (ambiguity, fragmentation, bad sequencing, state mismatch). Assume capacity often exists; fix **routing**, not activation.

## Canonical paths (only)

| What | Path |
|------|------|
| Xcode project | `App/Increments.xcodeproj` |
| Swift sources (8-file architecture) | `App/Increments/*.swift` |
| Master brief | `Docs/INCREMENTS_Master.md` |
| Voice / design doctrine | `Docs/INCREMENTS_Voice_Doctrine.md`, `Docs/INCREMENTS_Design_Decisions_v1.2.md` |
| Psych / profile references | `Psych/` (PDFs — not app code) |
| Historical docs | `Archive/Past-Docs/` |

Do **not** open `INCREMENTS New Top Folder`, duplicate Xcode projects, or `Archive/Past-Docs/Increments/` snapshots unless explicitly doing archaeology.

## Read first (doctrine before code)

1. `Docs/INCREMENTS_Master.md` — architecture, behavioral model, tab/system ownership
2. `Docs/INCREMENTS_Voice_Doctrine.md` — presence layer (Jarvis/Alfred register; observed evidence only)
3. `Docs/INCREMENTS_Design_Decisions_v1.2.md` — visual/type constraints when touching UI

When **FORM-iOS** is in the same workspace: borrow **layout restraint and hierarchy** from `FORM-iOS/docs/form_system_doctrine.md` only — never FORM athlete voice, Forge copy, or training-session patterns.

For **workspace-wide strategy**: targeted sections of `FORM-iOS/docs/BRICE_OS/BRICE_OPERATOR_PRODUCT_BRIEF.md` only when cross-product — not for local INCREMENTS UI tasks.

## Domain boundaries (do not collapse)

| Domain | Owns | Do not merge into |
|--------|------|-------------------|
| **Today** | Execute — sequence, doors, maintenance, daily review | Operator theory dumps on Home |
| **Operator** | Improve routing — cognition lab, brief, dossier, consult | Motivational copy or generic task apps |
| **Capital** | Runway, reserves, financial state | Hideout shift logistics |
| **Hideout** | Venue/business system (shifts, building context) | `hideout-ops-console` analytics theater |
| **Physique** | Body composition / training-adjacent personal signal | FORM Forge programming or athlete Today |

**hideout-ops-console** is a separate repo (venue operator instrument). INCREMENTS Hideout tab is Brice’s embedded business context — do not port console dashboards or fake intelligence here.

## Hard guardrails

- **Not motivation, routing.** No hype, streaks, guilt, “you’ve got this,” or participation-gap framing unless Master/Voice explicitly reopens it.
- **Evidence before speech.** Wendy/presence lines only from observable inputs — same discipline as FORM voice doctrine, different character.
- **No slot-filling intelligence.** Empty is correct when no signal exists.
- **Do not hardcode temporary hypotheses as doctrine.** Observed model corrections belong in Master + Voice docs first, then `IntelligenceLayer.swift` — not one-off strings in views.
- **No generic productivity drift.** No Notion-style feature creep, gamification, social, or “AI summary of your week” unless specced in Master.
- **iPad / readability.** Primary device is iPad-class canvas: preserve generous spacing, readable type under low capacity (Reserve days), mono for metadata only per design decisions — do not crush density to look “premium.”

## Out of scope unless explicitly requested

- RunCards, FORM Forge catalogs, Mason/Jose program libraries
- Hideout ops console feature parity
- Cross-app refactors that touch more than one BRICE-OS root in a single drive-by

## Workspace

**BRICE-OS** — open `FORM-iOS/BRICE-OS.code-workspace`. Canonical; `FORM-Speed-Hideout.code-workspace` is legacy alias only.
